<TEXT>
Sir, Matthew Kaminski's article, 'Feathered herds give heavyweight profits'
(July 29), talked about ostriches being 'first introduced . . . in the
mid-1980s' to the US.
In fact, ostrich farms abounded in south-west US more than 70 years or so
ago. I recall seeing several old photographs of ostrich farms in Arizona.
This is not a new phenomenon, merely an old one revived.
