<HEADLINE>
FT  09 AUG 93 / PSBR figure is challenged
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
THE PUBLIC sector borrowing requirement may not be as big as the government
maintains, Mr Frank Dobson, shadow employment secretary, said yesterday.
Pointing to last week's official revision of last year's balance of payments
figures which showed the current account deficit was nearly Pounds 3bn
smaller than the government originally estimated, Mr Dobson said the present
Pounds 50bn PSBR estimate might be 'artificially high'.
He said it would 'suit' ministers to overstate the scale of the public
spending problem and would 'soften up the public to accept as inevitable the
Tory attack on the welfare state'.
</TEXT>
