FT  09 AUG 93 / Retailers lead field in deals abroad
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By NEIL BUCKLEY
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
RETAILERS based in the UK dominated first-time expansion in the north-west
of continental Europe last year, research by Management Horizons, the retail
research group, has indicated, Neil Buckley writes.
UK retailers accounted for 25 per cent of deals in which retailers were
expanding into a north-western European market for the first time. Retailers
in France, the Netherlands and Switzerland each accounted for less than 15
per cent.
The UK companies included Tesco, which acquired the French supermarket chain
Catteau, and Sears, which bought the Dutch mail order operator Ter Meulen
Post.
The UK, France and Germany each accounted for 20 per cent of first-time
expansion activity in Europe as a whole.
European Retail Expansion. Management Horizons, Waverley House, Lower
Square, Isleworth, London TW7 6RL.
