<HEADLINE>
FT  07 AUG 93 / Bonn sets air talks deadline
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   BONN
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Germany, which has threatened to cancel its civil aviation agreement with
the US, has set a September 15 deadline for talks on a new bilateral accord,
Reuter reports from Bonn.
The German Transport Ministry has also proposed a seven-year interim pact,
it said. This would restrict US airline activity in Germany ahead of a final
negotiated treaty to be implemented in the year 2000.
