FT  07 AUG 93 / Finance and the Family: Surveys agree, house prices are
inching up - At a glance
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
HOUSE prices rose by a seasonally-adjusted 0.9 per cent in July after falls
in May and June, according to the Halifax house price index. Nationwide
found that prices rose by 0.7 per cent in July, the fifth monthly rise in
succession according to its index.
Adrian Coles, director-general of the Council of Mortgage Lenders, said that
the housing market was slowly recovering and that recent mortgage lending
figures were 'very encouraging'. The figures released by the council this
week show that net new lending rose to Pounds 4.1bn in the second quarter,
up from Pounds 2.9bn in the first quarter. However, the second quarter
figure is still lower than the Pounds 5.2bn of net new advances for the same
period last year.
