<HEADLINE>
FT  07 AUG 93 / International Company News: Sharp rise at Berliner Bank
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By JUDY DEMPSEY
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   BERLIN
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
BERLINER Bank, Germany's tenth-largest private commercial bank, announced a
sharp increase in operating profits and net trading income for the first six
months of the year compared with the same period last year, writes Judy
Dempsey in Berlin.
Group partial operating profits rose to DM285.7m (Dollars 166.1m), against
DM188.4m, while parent partial operating profits increased to DM244.5m from
DM172.7m. Net trading income rose by DM6m to DM24.7m. Risk provisions, which
totalled DM140.1m during the 1992 first half, fell 41 per cent to DM100m for
the same period this year.
