<HEADLINE>
FT  07 AUG 93 / UK Company News: de Morgan cuts loss to Pounds 258,000
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Pre-tax losses at de Morgan Group were reduced from Pounds 1.71m to Pounds
258,000 in the year ended April 30.
Mr Patrick Cooper, chairman, said turnover in both core activities of
property investment and finance advice had improved significantly.
Turnover came to Pounds 1.91m (Pounds 1.38m) producing an operating loss of
Pounds 293,000 (Pounds 1.73m).
Net borrowings fell from Pounds 70,000 to Pounds 24,000.
The chairman said that in recent months the number and value of property
transactions had shown a marked increase.
Losses per share came to 0.54p (3.06p).
</TEXT>
