and 30 per cent shareholder, were not prepared to meet the requirement.
In February, the group returned an annual pre-tax profit of Pounds 2.45m,
against a loss of Pounds 17.5m.
Dunkeld has debt of about Pounds 7m, the legacy of rapid expansion in the
1980s when borrowing rose to Pounds 16m.
