FT  07 AUG 93 / White-collar tendering review
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
COOPERS &amp; LYBRAND, the accountancy firm, has been appointed by the
Department of the Environment to study how compulsory competitive tendering
can be introduced to local-authority white-collar services.
Competitive tendering is already compulsory for a range of manual services,
but is yet to be introduced for legal services and 'construction-related
services' such as quantity surveying and architecture. Security guards at
the Sheffield offices of the Department of Employment are to strike from
Monday as part of the NUCPS Civil Service union's dispute over market
testing.
